# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#1013, Pipfile.lock should not be ignored in most cases.
#   If you have a "multi-platform" project, or dependencies are to be installed using
#   `pipenv install --dev`, then keeping it in version control is a good idea.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock should generally be tracked in version control.
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock should generally be tracked in version control.
#pdm.lock

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

